FishEye shows deleted SVN directories as undeleted.

*Steps to reproduce:*
# Checkout from the repository:
{noformat}
svn checkout https://example.com/svn/PROJECT
{noformat}
# Navigate to the project, create an empty directory, and commit changes:
{noformat}
cd PROJECT
mkdir delete-me
svn add ./delete-me
svn commit -m "Adding delete-me directory"
{noformat}
# Create a text file inside this directory and commit changes:
{noformat}
echo delete me > ./delete-me/delete-me.txt
cd ./delete-me
svn commit -m "Adding delete-me file."
{noformat}
# File {{delete-me.txt}} shows up in FishEye.
# Delete the file from the directory and commit changes:
{noformat}
svn del ./delete-me.txt
svn commit -m "Removing delete-me file."
{noformat}
# File {{delete-me.txt}} no longer shows up in FishEye.
# Delete the directory and commit changes:
{noformat}
cd ..
svn del ./delete-me
svn commit -m "Removing delete-me dir."
{noformat}
# FishEye still shows a yellowish {{delete-me}} directory (instead of a greyish directory, meaning that it's empty), and "Hide empty directories" does not work. It behaves as the directory is not empty.

